## Key Takeaways (SOC Tier 1)

- **SIEM = SIM + SEM** — centralise, normalise, correlate, alert.
- **Parsing** (log → fields) vs **Normalisation** (all logs → one format). Normalised logs are *why* field-value detection rules work.
- **Host-centric** (inside a machine) vs **network-centric** (between machines).
- **Event ID 104** = logs cleared; **Event ID 4688** = process execution.
- The job is the **True vs False Positive** call → false = tune, true = investigate + contain.
- Splunk agent = **Forwarder**; ingestion = Agent / Syslog / Manual Upload / Port-Forwarding.

